1 packet Creamy Pesto Dressing
1 Red Onion
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
4 herbed pork sausage
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 Carrot
1 Parsnip
1 packet Peeled Pumpkin Pieces
1 drizzle olive oil
1 drizzle balsamic vinegar

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut parsnip and carrot into bite-sized chunks. Cut onion (see ingredients) into wedges.
• Place parsnip, carrot, onion and peeled pumpkin pieces on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, sprinkle over garlic & herb seasoning, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.
Little cooks: Help toss the veggies

• Meanwhile, place herbed pork sausages on a second lined oven tray, drizzle with olive oil and turn to coat.
• Bake until cooked through, 12-16 minutes.

• When veggies are done, add baby leaves and a drizzle of balsamic vinegar to the tray. Season to taste and toss to combine.

• Divide roast veggie toss between plates.
• Top with pork sausages. Drizzle over creamy pesto dressing to serve. Enjoy!
Little cooks: Add the finishing touch by drizzling over the dressing!